{"type":"text","timestamp":1781128749404,"sessionID":"ses_14c74eea9ffeIyeKUQdOD4vWgF","part":{"id":"prt_eb38bcb63001WvydE6w5hMRhIy","messageID":"msg_eb38bb390001c5gCGhaLB0083u","sessionID":"ses_14c74eea9ffeIyeKUQdOD4vWgF","type":"text","text":"I found only `.executor-state/` under the lineage directory, so this is a fresh lineage packet. I’m moving into init by discovering the target spec docs and implementation references before writing the lineage state files.","time":{"start":1781128743779,"end":1781128749400},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08db5490f2bf96f8016a29de27ca488191b7e85a646ef3724d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781128749607,"sessionID":"ses_14c74eea9ffeIyeKUQdOD4vWgF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_y9UPnQHl16wVYj4YbSMiBCvh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"target_files|Target Files|Files|\\.ts|\\.js|\\.md|\\.json|\\.yaml","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 427 matches (showing first 100)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/005-advisor-feedback-calibration/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 34: <!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md -->\n\n  Line 57:      NO \"Files Changed\" table for Level 3/3+. The narrative IS the summary.\n\n  Line 58:      For Level 1-2, a Files Changed table after the narrative is fine.\n\n  Line 59:      Reference: specs/system-spec-kit/020-mcp-working-memory-hybrid-rag/implementation-summary.md -->\n\n  Line 71: ### Files Changed\n\n  Line 77: | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/feedback-calibration.ts` | Created | Adds the default-off reducer, guardrails, and advisory record persistence |\n\n  Line 78: | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/weights-config.ts` | Modified | Adds a read-only proposal builder while leaving live defaults unchanged |\n\n  Line 79: | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/handlers/advisor-validate.ts` | Modified | Records shadow calibration reports from validate outcomes only when enabled |\n\n  Line 80: | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/scorer/advisor-feedback-calibration.vitest.ts` | Created | Covers reducer behavior and byte-identical live scoring with flag off vs on |\n\n  Line 81: | `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/handlers/advisor-validate.vitest.ts` | Modified | Covers validate-handler report recording under the explicit shadow flag |\n\n  Line 82: | `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/005-advisor-feedback-calibration/{spec.md,plan.md,tasks.md,implementation-summary.md}` | Modified | Reconciles phase status, tasks, continuity, and evidence |\n\n  Line 120:      \"FAIL, TS2349 error in benchmarks.ts\" not \"Minor issues detected.\" -->\n\n  Line 124: | `npm run test -- tests/scorer/advisor-feedback-calibration.vitest.ts tests/handlers/advisor-validate.vitest.ts` | PASS: 2 files, 11 tests |\n\n  Line 127: | `npm run test` | BASELINE FAIL: 73 passed, 1 skipped, 1 failed file, 451 passed tests, 5 skipped, 35 failed in known out-of-scope `tests/hooks/settings-driven-invocation-parity.vitest.ts` |\n\n  Line 152: HVR rules: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/005-advisor-feedback-calibration/plan.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Phase 5: advisor-feedback-calibration [template:level_1/plan.md]\"\n\n  Line 103: | `advisor-validate.ts` | Records validate outcomes and builds validation telemetry | Added default-off shadow report recording | Targeted validate handler test writes one advisory report only when enabled |\n\n  Line 104: | `weights-config.ts` | Owns live scorer weights | Added read-only proposal builder; live defaults unchanged | Reducer tests assert `DEFAULT_SCORER_WEIGHTS` remains unchanged |\n\n  Line 105: | `feedback-calibration.ts` | New reducer surface | Created advisory reducer, sample guards, and bounded JSONL record path | Reducer tests cover default-off, low sample, concentration, and proposed deltas |\n\n  Line 109: - Same-class producers: inspected `advisor-validate.ts`, `metrics.ts`, and `weights-config.ts` outcome/weight ownership.\n\n  Line 110: - Consumers of changed symbols: new reducer is consumed by `advisor-validate.ts` and targeted tests only.\n\n  Line 126: - [x] Added `feedback-calibration.ts` with default-off shadow gating, sample guards, report persistence, and no-auto-promotion metadata\n\n  Line 127: - [x] Added read-only proposed-vs-current weights and threshold proposal builder in `weights-config.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/005-advisor-feedback-calibration/tasks.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Tasks: Phase 5: advisor-feedback-calibration [template:level_1/tasks.md]\"\n\n  Line 96: - **Specification**: See `spec.md`\n\n  Line 97: - **Plan**: See `plan.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/005-advisor-feedback-calibration/spec.md:\n  Line 54: | **Parent Spec** | ../spec.md |\n\n  Line 88: The advisor already accepts accepted/corrected/ignored outcome events through `advisor_validate` (`schemas/advisor-tool-schemas.ts:240-250`), but nothing consumes them, so real routing feedback is discarded. Memory's 027 reducers are shadow/default-off and demonstrate the safe pattern (`027 before-vs-after.md:135-145`).\n\n  Line 109: ### Files to Change\n\n  Line 113: | `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/handlers/advisor-validate.ts` | Modify | Feed recorded outcomes into the shadow reducer |\n\n  Line 114: | `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/weights-config.ts` | Modify | Read-only \"proposed weights\" surface; no live mutation |\n\n  Line 115: | `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/feedback-calibration.ts` | Create | Aggregate outcomes into advisory calibration reports and persisted shadow records |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/009-codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver/tasks.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Tasks: Phase 9: codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver [template:level_1/tasks.md]\"\n\n  Line 19:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts\"\n\n  Line 22:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 69: - [x] T004 Implement `symbol-bm25-resolver.ts` packed BM25F index over symbol fields\n\n  Line 70: - [x] T005 Add `querySymbolIndexRows()` read-only accessor in `code-graph-db.ts`\n\n  Line 92: - [x] Verification passed with recorded command evidence in `implementation-summary.md`\n\n  Line 100: - **Specification**: See `spec.md`\n\n  Line 101: - **Plan**: See `plan.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/009-codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Summary [template:level_1/implementation-summary.md]\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts\"\n\n  Line 22:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 24:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 39: <!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr_rules.md -->\n\n  Line 66: ### Files Changed\n\n  Line 70: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts` | Created | Packed BM25F symbol candidate resolver with default-off flag parser |\n\n  Line 71: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts` | Modified | Additive read-only accessor for symbol fields |\n\n  Line 72: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts` | Modified | Emits BM25 suggestions only after exact subject matching misses and the flag is enabled |\n\n  Line 73: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts` | Created | Covers field weighting, near-miss scoring, packed postings, and flag parsing |\n\n  Line 74: | `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts` | Modified | Proves exact-match byte identity and fallback-only query behavior |\n\n  Line 94: | Do not wire `code_graph_context` internals in this phase | The user explicitly disallowed `lib/code-graph-context.ts` and `handlers/context.ts`; the resolver module is reusable for seed suggestions without touching those files. |\n\n  Line 104: | `npm test -- --run mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts` | PASS: 2 files, 43 tests |\n\n  Line 105: | `npm test -- --run mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts mcp_server/tests/query-intent-classifier.vitest.ts mcp_server/tests/handlers/classify-query-intent.vitest.ts` | PASS: 3 files, 54 tests |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/009-codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver/spec.md:\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts\"\n\n  Line 22:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 24:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 57: | **Parent Spec** | ../spec.md |\n\n  Line 72: **Scope Boundary**: Subject resolution in `handlers/query.ts`. Add an optional BM25/BM25F resolver over symbol fields (`name`, `fq_name`, `signature`, `docstring`, file path) used only when exact equality fails or is ambiguous, or to suggest `code_graph_context` seeds. Exact-match behavior stays primary and unchanged.\n\n  Line 91: Code-graph subject matching is exact equality on `fq_name` or `name` (`handlers/query.ts:202-235`), so a near-miss symbol query returns nothing and the caller has no disambiguation help. A BM25/BM25F resolver over symbol fields would handle fuzzy lookup, but the code graph is intentionally structural - the analysis flags the real risk of competing with Grep for text search.\n\n  Line 112: ### Files to Change\n\n  Line 116: | `system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts` (~:202-235) | Modified | Fall back to symbol suggestions only when exact subject matching returns no symbol and the opt-in flag is enabled |\n\n  Line 117: | `system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts` | Modified | Added a read-only symbol-field row accessor for resolver indexing |\n\n  Line 118: | `system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts` | Created | Packed BM25F index over symbol fields for disambiguation-only candidates |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/009-codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver/plan.md:\n  Line 2: title: \"Implementation Plan: Phase 9: codegraph-bm25-symbol-resolver [template:level_1/plan.md]\"\n\n  Line 20:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/symbol-bm25-resolver.ts\"\n\n  Line 21:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/handlers/query.ts\"\n\n  Line 22:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/lib/code-graph-db.ts\"\n\n  Line 23:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 24:       - \".opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/tests/code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts\"\n\n  Line 83: - **`symbol-bm25-resolver.ts`**: Builds a packed in-memory BM25F index over symbol fields and returns symbol candidates only.\n\n  Line 84: - **`query.ts` exact resolver**: Preserves exact resolution and calls BM25 only on unresolved subjects when the feature flag is enabled.\n\n  Line 85: - **`code-graph-db.ts` accessor**: Exposes symbol rows for the fallback index without mutating graph storage.\n\n  Line 88: Query subject -> exact `symbol_id` lookup -> exact `fq_name` lookup -> exact `name` lookup -> unchanged structural query when any exact match exists. Only when all exact paths miss and `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_BM25_SYMBOL_RESOLVER` is enabled, `query.ts` loads symbol-field rows and returns BM25 candidate suggestions in the unresolved-subject error payload.\n\n  Line 98: | `query.ts` subject resolution | Owns exact `symbol_id` / `fq_name` / `name` matching | Updated only after exact miss | Byte-identical exact-match test in `code-graph-query-handler.vitest.ts` |\n\n  Line 99: | `symbol-bm25-resolver.ts` | Scores symbol candidates | New default-off fallback helper | `symbol-bm25-resolver.vitest.ts` covers weights, trigrams, packed arrays, and flag parser |\n\n  Line 100: | `code-graph-db.ts` | Reads graph rows | Additive read-only accessor | Typecheck and query tests |\n\n  Line 103: - Same-class producers checked: existing exact matching in `handlers/query.ts`; packed BM25 pattern in advisor scorer.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/145-xce-feature-adoption-advisor-codegraph/004-advisor-bfs-consolidation/tasks.md:\n  Line 20:       - \".opencod